The paper presents a new robotic harvester for sweet peppers that uses vision algorithms and a novel end-effector design. The focus is on reducing labour costs and improving crop quality, scheduling, and profit. The paper discusses field trials and the efficacy of the approach. The paper's content is related to robotics (cs.RO), computer vision (cs.CV), machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and systems and control (cs.SY).
